04:57.839 --> 05:00.012
Oh, look who's here.

05:02.511 --> 05:04.058
Finally...

05:04.221 --> 05:05.063
Hey!

05:05.514 --> 05:06.857
You must be the Cassidys?

05:07.015 --> 05:08.141
- Yes.
- Dan.

05:08.308 --> 05:09.525
Hi, Dan.

05:09.684 --> 05:10.901
- Dan Gifford.
- How are you?

05:11.061 --> 05:12.358
So sorry, I'm late.

05:12.521 --> 05:15.115
I left my cell at the office.
I'm sure you tried to call.

05:15.273 --> 05:17.617
- I did. Fifteen times.
- Oh, sorry about that.

05:17.776 --> 05:18.868
(FORCED LAUGHTER)

05:19.027 --> 05:21.029
- Let me show you your new home.
- Yes, great.

05:21.196 --> 05:24.291
DAN: I just got to dig up the key here.

05:24.449 --> 05:25.792
How was the drive?

05:26.493 --> 05:30.293
WOMAN: Oh, we were on the road for two
days. Kind of anxious to get settled.

05:30.622 --> 05:32.795
Well, I think you'll be
very comfortable here.

05:32.958 --> 05:34.801
And you'll love the neighborhood.

05:34.960 --> 05:37.304
- Wow...
- Which reminds me...

05:37.462 --> 05:39.635
It's ginormous.

05:44.469 --> 05:45.766
DAN: If you have any problems,
just give me a call.

05:45.929 --> 05:48.682
- Great. Thanks.
- See you at the potluck.

05:49.432 --> 05:51.184
Mom, this is beautiful.

05:51.351 --> 05:53.194
That is all state park.

05:53.353 --> 05:56.323
Can you believe it?
Good backyard, huh?

05:56.481 --> 05:58.654
Ls that Mr. and Mrs.
Dead People's house?

06:01.444 --> 06:03.822
Oh, wow...

06:05.448 --> 06:07.951
I didn't realize it was so close.

06:09.077 --> 06:11.000
GIRL: Nobody lives there, right?

06:11.162 --> 06:12.379
No.

06:12.956 --> 06:14.674
No, the place is empty.

06:16.376 --> 06:19.425
You know, that house is the reason
we can even afford to rent this house.

06:19.588 --> 06:21.215
- Really?
- Yeah.

06:21.381 --> 06:24.430
Double murder, kind of a drag
on the real estate market.

06:24.593 --> 06:28.439
(SCOFFS) People got shot on our block,
nobody ever cut our rent.

06:29.764 --> 06:31.391
Come on, help me unpack.

06:31.558 --> 06:34.437
OK. I just want to look around, first.

06:34.603 --> 06:35.855
All right, fine.

07:24.361 --> 07:27.911
(RUSTLING, BIRD SCREECHING,
WINGS FLAPPING)

07:31.660 --> 07:33.708
(TWIG CRACKS)

07:54.057 --> 07:55.650
WOMAN: Thanks for cooking.

07:55.809 --> 07:58.858
Thank Daddy, he's the one
who taught me how to make this.

07:59.354 --> 08:02.949
Boil the water and put in spaghetti,
and... open the jar thing?

08:03.108 --> 08:05.361
Wow. What a great dad he is.

08:05.527 --> 08:08.872
It's not like you carry that lighter
around because you miss smoking.

08:13.159 --> 08:15.082
Yeah, I miss him sometimes.

08:15.495 --> 08:18.044
I missed him when we were married.

08:18.206 --> 08:20.129
He was on the road
nine months out of the year.

08:31.219 --> 08:33.472
I think this place is going to be
really good for us.

08:36.850 --> 08:40.229
It's just gonna take some time
for me to get used to having you around.

08:43.523 --> 08:44.900
I gave you the biggest room.

08:45.066 --> 08:48.741
- How hard's it going to be?
- (CHUCKLES)

08:48.903 --> 08:50.871
(LAUGHS)

09:14.137 --> 09:17.266
(SOFT THUDDING)

09:28.318 --> 09:31.788
(DISTANT CLATTERING)

