10:08.358 --> 10:12.579
Um, everyone... This is Sarah Cassidy
and her daughter Elissa.

10:12.737 --> 10:15.957
They're our new neighbors.
They're renting the Reeds' place.

10:16.116 --> 10:19.461
- Welcome to the neighborhood.
- Thank you.

10:19.619 --> 10:22.372
- I made some potato salad.
- Oh, great. Great.

10:22.539 --> 10:26.464
Elissa, do you like to swim?
Pool's at 95. It's like Aruba.

10:26.626 --> 10:28.503
-Hi.
-Hi... Dan...

10:28.670 --> 10:32.470
- Yeah.
- The, um, Jacobson house...

10:32.632 --> 10:34.179
Is anyone living there?

10:34.342 --> 10:36.765
Because late last night
I saw a light go on.

10:36.928 --> 10:39.807
Oh, that'd be Ryan Jacobson, the son.

10:40.723 --> 10:43.317
Really? But you said
it was going to be empty.

10:43.476 --> 10:46.980
No, the son lives there.
ls that a problem?

10:48.231 --> 10:49.528
No.

10:49.691 --> 10:52.535
Good, good.
I mean, we do have a signed lease.

10:52.694 --> 10:54.867
- (SARAH CHUCKLES)
- MAN: There you go.

10:55.029 --> 10:56.030
- Oh, thank you.
- Thanks.

10:56.197 --> 10:58.040
- BOY: Marco!
- CHILDREN: Polo!

10:58.199 --> 10:59.621
- Marco!
- Polo!

10:59.784 --> 11:03.254
That's my son, Tyler.
Honor roll. Student council.

11:03.413 --> 11:05.916
Him and his friends
started this group last year,

11:06.082 --> 11:07.675
famine relief program.

11:07.834 --> 11:11.054
