20:56.088 --> 20:58.216
My dad was in a rock band.

21:02.511 --> 21:04.354
You got anything good?

21:05.681 --> 21:07.854
Still using cassettes.

21:08.017 --> 21:09.360
(LAUGHS)

21:09.518 --> 21:12.692
Dude, we got to get you
some new music.

21:12.855 --> 21:14.402
Yeah.

21:17.359 --> 21:18.952
I used to have one of these.

21:21.614 --> 21:23.958
Yeah, that was my dad's.

21:24.116 --> 21:25.914
So was this car.

21:29.371 --> 21:32.625
So are you and your mom
in Woodshire to stay?

21:32.792 --> 21:34.214
I hope so.

21:56.273 --> 21:58.367
It's so quiet here.

21:59.068 --> 22:01.070
Not like where I used to live.

22:03.572 --> 22:05.700
It's even quieter at dawn.

22:05.866 --> 22:09.211
Dawn? What are you doing up that early?

22:12.456 --> 22:15.551
I Sit Out back and I Write Stuff.

22:16.418 --> 22:19.513
Like stories. it's easy.

22:21.173 --> 22:24.768
I don't know, it's like...
it's like at that time of the day,

22:24.927 --> 22:27.646
because everyone is still asleep,

22:27.805 --> 22:30.228
all the best thoughts
haven't been taken yet.

22:35.646 --> 22:38.570
(PHONE RING-S)

22:41.277 --> 22:45.123
It's my mom. I better go.

22:45.948 --> 22:48.201
Thank you, for driving me.

22:48.367 --> 22:51.337
Yeah, you're welcome.

23:06.719 --> 23:08.972
- Hey.
- Hi.

23:09.138 --> 23:12.187
Did Tyler's mom give you a ride home?

23:12.349 --> 23:14.727
No. Actually, Ryan Jacobson did.

23:14.894 --> 23:19.695
Ryan Jacobson?
How did Ryan Jacobson give you a ride?

23:20.232 --> 23:22.030
No one wanted to give me a ride,

23:22.192 --> 23:26.117
