- Nice to meet you.

28:26.121 --> 28:27.714
Bye.

28:28.165 --> 28:31.544
- He likes you.
-I already got a job.

28:32.961 --> 28:34.804
Excuse me, Officer!

28:34.963 --> 28:36.806
Hey, did I forget to sign something?

28:36.965 --> 28:39.639
Oh, no, no.
I just wanted to ask you something.

28:39.801 --> 28:43.055
- I'm Sarah, Sarah Cassidy.
- Bill Weaver, what's up?

28:43.222 --> 28:45.941
I just moved here with my daughter,
who's 17,

28:46.099 --> 28:48.147
and we have a rental on Sycamore Lane.

28:48.310 --> 28:50.233
And you wanted to know
if I thought it was possible

28:50.395 --> 28:53.945
you had a 17-year-old daughter.
I would have to say no.

28:54.107 --> 28:56.826
It's actually about Ryan Jacobson.

28:56.985 --> 28:59.238
He drove my daughter home
the other night.

28:59.404 --> 29:03.125
I was just wondering if you
knew anything about him. If he's...

29:03.283 --> 29:04.079
OK?

29:04.952 --> 29:06.124
Yeah.

29:06.620 --> 29:08.748
Finding out that your parents
were murdered,

29:08.914 --> 29:12.794
by your own sister, God,
that's really intense.

29:12.960 --> 29:16.134
You'd think people would show him
a little bit of sympathy, right?

29:17.089 --> 29:20.844
You know, I drove three hours upstate
personally to tell Ryan.

29:21.009 --> 29:23.478
He was living with his aunt,
a senile old woman.

29:23.637 --> 29:27.562
He had no one taking care of him.
He was taking care of her, actually.

29:27.724 --> 29:31.069
Anyway, he moved back here with her,
she died about a year ago.

29:31.228 --> 29:34.823
The Kid's had a tough, tough life.

29:34.982 --> 29:37.701
Look, I've never had
any problem with him,

29:37.859 --> 29:39.657
and as far as I know,
no one else has either.

29:39.820 --> 29:43.199
But they sure like to bitch about him
and their property values, don't they?

29:43.365 --> 29:46.118
Yeah, I have heard people doing that.

29:46.285 --> 29:48.583
- 710-49 at Main and Jackson. Over.
- Excuse me.

29:48.745 --> 29:50.292
OK.

29:50.455 --> 29:53.004
Sorry. I gotta go.

29:55.377 --> 29:56.469
Thanks, officer.

29:56.628 --> 29:59.848
Oh, hey, no.
it's, uh, Bill, OK?

30:00.340 --> 30:01.216
Bill.

30:02.134 --> 30:03.932
- I'll see you around?
- Yeah.

30:36.335 --> 30:38.303
- Hi.
- Hey.

30:39.463 --> 30:42.216
I... made you a CD.

30:44.343 --> 30:45.845
Wow, thank you.

30:49.931 --> 30:51.899
Oh, my gosh, my page.

30:53.185 --> 30:56.109
Yeah... I wanted to listen
to some more of your music.

30:58.648 --> 31:00.241
That's not weird, is it?

31:00.400 --> 31:03.404
No. Not unless you didn't like it.

31:03.570 --> 31:08.076
No, actually,
I thought it was beautiful.

31:09.242 --> 31:12.246
Good answer. Whoa!

31:12.829 --> 31:15.457
Stocking up
the old fallout shelter, huh?

31:16.833 --> 31:20.804
Um, yeah. I don't like to go to town
more than I have to.

31:39.147 --> 31:42.822
Wow, it's big.

31:47.155 --> 31:48.577
What's up there?

31:48.740 --> 31:51.459
Construction never really got finished
on this part of the house.

31:51.618 --> 31:57.625
I don't have a wall or anything,
but I moved back here when I came back.

31:58.625 --> 32:00.673
It's a little bit small.

32:00.836 --> 32:03.589
Well, at least you're not a sleepwalker.

32:05.132 --> 32:08.352
- ls this the family?
- Yeah.

32:10.637 --> 32:12.890
Oh, Ryan, you're so cute.

32:14.307 --> 32:16.901
And that's Carrie Anne.

32:17.060 --> 32:19.904
Wow. Her eyes are so blue.

32:22.149 --> 32:24.743
Your family looks really happy.

32:26.319 --> 32:30.290
It must've been nice,
having everyone together.

32:31.658 --> 32:33.331
Having two parents.

32:35.954 --> 32:38.457
Carrie Anne was the head of the family.

32:40.041 --> 32:42.294
After the accident, things changed.

32:44.671 --> 32:46.469
Is that when they sent you away?

32:50.677 --> 32:53.931
I've never really talked to anyone
about this stuff before.

32:59.060 --> 33:00.152
ELISSA: What's in here?

33:06.693 --> 33:08.866
I'm so sorry. I shouldn't have...

33:09.029 --> 33:10.952
It's OK, you don't have to go.

33:12.240 --> 33:14.493
I haven't been in here in a long time.

33:21.082 --> 33:22.959
ELISSA: I thought she was 13.

33:24.085 --> 33:25.928
This looks like a little kid's room.

33:28.298 --> 33:30.392
She had brain damage.

33:36.973 --> 33:39.101
- RYAN: We were just playing.
- (GIRL GIGGLING)

33:39.809 --> 33:41.811
Like we did most days.

33:41.978 --> 33:44.481
We ran around, we'd play tag.

33:45.273 --> 33:47.367
Her favorite thing
was to play on the swings.

33:50.570 --> 33:52.538
My mom and dad were inside.

33:53.573 --> 33:55.575
I was supposed to be watching her.

33:57.410 --> 33:59.458
But she kept wanting to get higher.

34:04.209 --> 34:05.961
(GIGGLING)

34:07.504 --> 34:08.630
(INHALING)

34:15.094 --> 34:16.768
Mom!

34:24.271 --> 34:26.273
RYAN: When she woke up,
she was different.

34:29.568 --> 34:31.866
She used to scream all the time,

34:32.027 --> 34:35.998
and she would attack us
and break things.

34:36.449 --> 34:39.202
Is that why there are bars
on all the windows?

34:39.369 --> 34:40.416
Yeah.

34:40.579 --> 34:44.379
She never knew where she was.
She would...

34:44.541 --> 34:50.047
She'd run out into the woods.
They were to keep her in.

34:54.509 --> 34:57.262
Now they just keep the townies
from coming down here.

34:59.306 --> 35:01.354
I don't really like coming
into this part of the house.

35:17.574 --> 35:22.501
Well, thank you.
And I hope you like the CD.

35:22.662 --> 35:24.255
Yeah. Thank you.

35:26.499 --> 35:28.001
- Bye.
- Bye.

36:12.003 --> 36:13.755
(SIGHS)

36:14.214 --> 36:17.684
(GIGGLING)

36:32.565 --> 36:33.908
Elissa?

36:34.567 --> 36:35.910
Can you come help me?

36:36.820 --> 36:38.788
- I have to go to work.
- Hey.

36:38.947 --> 36:40.244
Thanks.

36:41.074 --> 36:43.042
- How was school?
- Mm...

36:43.201 --> 36:45.078
School's school. How's work?

36:45.245 --> 36:48.590
It's OK. I don't know.
The late shifts are kind of tough.

36:48.748 --> 36:52.423
But I like being in the hospital.
I like the drama.

36:52.585 --> 36:54.679
- (BOTH CHUCKLE)
- What did you do after school?

36:55.880 --> 37:00.602
I, um...
dropped off a CD at Ryan's house.

37:01.302 --> 37:04.181
And he's really sweet...

37:04.347 --> 37:05.644
...and sad...

37:05.807 --> 37:07.809
...and lonely, all at the same time.

37:07.976 --> 37:10.320
He's all by himself in this big house,
with the shades drawn.

37:10.478 --> 37:12.572
You went to his house?

37:12.731 --> 37:15.109
We dropped 'shrooms
and had unprotected sex.

37:17.235 --> 37:19.613
- I know what you're doing.
- What?

37:19.779 --> 37:21.622
- You're trying to save him.
- I am not.

37:21.781 --> 37:23.533
Yes, you are. That's what you do,
you like to fix people.

37:23.700 --> 37:25.327
Oh, yaddayadda-yadda.

37:25.493 --> 37:28.121
Honey, sometimes
people can't be fixed.

37:36.504 --> 37:39.178
(PANTING)

37:55.523 --> 37:58.151
(DOOR RATTLING)

38:11.498 --> 38:16.379
- (ELECTRICAL FIZZLING)
- (MOANING)

38:19.881 --> 38:22.600
(SCREECHING)

38:39.067 --> 38:41.445
(TYPING)

38:48.952 --> 38:52.331
(WHEEZING, MOANING)

39:04.133 --> 39:06.261
(GRUNTING)

39:10.306 --> 39:12.274
(GASPING, SCREECH ING)

39:21.442 --> 39:22.614
(PANTING)

39:26.364 --> 39:27.786
(GASPING)

39:32.245 --> 39:33.872
Carrie Anne, no! No!

39:35.915 --> 39:37.258
SARAH: See you after work, honey.

39:37.417 --> 39:38.714
- OK, bye.
- Bye.

40:46.653 --> 40:48.701
(RATTLING)

41:21.688 --> 41:22.905
(DOOR UNLOCKING)

41:40.498 --> 41:42.967
- <GASPING)
- (LAUGHS)

41:43.126 --> 41:44.298
Sorry.

41:44.544 --> 41:46.342
You scared the piss out of me!

41:47.714 --> 41:51.059
- How did you get in?
- You left the front door open.

41:55.346 --> 41:56.768
(GRUNTING)

42:00.852 --> 42:03.321
(MOANING)

42:04.355 --> 42:08.781
♪ Wake up good-lookin'
and I stay that way

42:08.943 --> 42:13.119
♪ I break a couple hearts
almost everyday

42:13.281 --> 42:17.707
♪ Behind the scenes
I'm better than I am on stage

42:17.869 --> 42:21.214
♪ Pick a book you like
And I'm your favorite page

42:21.372 --> 42:25.718
♪ If you don't know, you're gonna know

42:26.627 --> 42:28.550
♪ That I'm that girl... J'

42:31.340 --> 42:32.967
Mm. Smells good.

42:36.971 --> 42:38.769
(DOORBELL RINGS)

42:38.931 --> 42:39.932
Who's that?

42:43.144 --> 42:45.988
- What are you up to?
- (SARAH LAUGHS)

42:47.815 --> 42:49.863
- Hi.
- Hello.

42:50.026 --> 42:51.073
Ryan?

42:52.487 --> 42:55.331
Yeah, I thought it would be nice
if we all got to know each other.

42:56.532 --> 42:57.579
OK.

43:05.917 --> 43:10.468
And I lived with my Aunt Iris,
but she had a stroke when I was 18,

43:10.630 --> 43:14.305
so after she was hospitalized,
I came back here.

43:15.802 --> 43:16.894
Back home.

43:21.641 --> 43:22.642
SARAH: Such a big house.

43:25.061 --> 43:28.406
Must be difficult to pay the bills.

43:28.689 --> 43:32.489
(CLEARS THROAT) You don't...
You don't have to answer that.

43:35.822 --> 43:38.496
My parents inherited the house,
and a little money,

43:38.658 --> 43:44.006
so... when they died, I got it all.

43:44.622 --> 43:47.466
It's not a lot, but it's enough.

43:48.334 --> 43:50.962
And I go to Bridgeport Community
part time, so...

43:52.672 --> 43:55.016
It's not really the greatest school
in the world, I know,

43:55.174 --> 43:58.519
but I'm just trying to get my credits
in line so I can apply for pre-med.

44:00.513 --> 44:03.483
- I want to be a psychiatrist.
- BOTH: Wow.

44:03.641 --> 44:07.236
My mom went to a psychiatrist for a long
time after she broke up with my dad.

44:15.820 --> 44:18.539
Thank you very much
for cooking the meal, Mrs. Cassidy.

44:24.120 --> 44:26.498
- Let's get some dessert.
- Yes.

44:36.048 --> 44:37.846
I just wanted to say thank you.

44:40.887 --> 44:44.562
You're actually the first people
to invite me over since it happened.

44:44.891 --> 44:48.441
Oh... Of course.

44:50.521 --> 44:52.023
(SARAH CLEARS THROAT)

44:54.901 --> 44:57.324
I'm sorry, I need to say something.

44:58.154 --> 45:01.954
Ryan, Elissa has just started in
a new school, and I want her to do well,

45:02.116 --> 45:04.369
and it's really one of the reasons
we even moved here.

45:04.535 --> 45:06.208
And she is in high school
and you are in college...

45:06.370 --> 45:07.587
Mom, what is your point?

45:07.747 --> 45:10.125
I think Ryan knows
exactly what my point is.

45:10.291 --> 45:12.885
We are neighbors,
and I want us to be friends,

45:13.044 --> 45:16.344
but I just have one rule
that I need you to respect.

45:16.505 --> 45:19.008
I do not want the two of you to be alone

45:19.175 --> 45:21.803
in your house or this house
if I am not here.

45:21.969 --> 45:26.019
- You are never here.
- Well, I am here now.

45:28.184 --> 45:31.609
Ryan, can you respect that?

45:33.147 --> 45:34.194
Yes.

45:36.734 --> 45:39.237
- Thank you.
- I should go.

45:39.403 --> 45:41.701
No, Ryan. No, no, Ryan.

45:41.864 --> 45:43.707
No, no, no. You can stay.

45:43.866 --> 45:44.788
- Ryan, please.
- You can stay.

45:44.951 --> 45:47.670
You're really lucky to have a mother
who cares about you.

45:48.537 --> 45:52.041
Ryan, really, it's fine.
You can stay. Really...

45:52.208 --> 45:53.755
Thank you very much for dinner.

45:53.918 --> 45:56.637
No, I... I didn't mean...

45:58.089 --> 45:59.306
I said he could stay!

45:59.465 --> 46:01.968
No, you invite him over
just so you can throw him out?

46:02.134 --> 46:04.136
Honey, I wanted to protect you!

46:04.303 --> 46:08.308
Oh, good! After all these years,
you finally decided to be a parent!

46:11.143 --> 46:13.817
You know, just because you were some
wasted slut in high school,

46:13.980 --> 46:15.027
it doesn't mean I'm going to be.

46:21.112 --> 46:24.161
SARAH: Oh, God,
I invited him over last night,

46:24.323 --> 46:25.996
and then I threw him out

46:26.158 --> 46:28.661
and I told him I didn't want him
to be alone with Elissa.

46:28.828 --> 46:32.002
So Elissa's not talking to me,

46:32.164 --> 46:34.838
and I'm sure Ryan
thinks I'm against him,

46:35.001 --> 46:37.629
like everyone else
in this ridiculous town.

46:37.795 --> 46:39.843
Ryan's a smart kid, I'm sure he gets it.

46:41.340 --> 46:44.219
I mean, I'm not stupid.
I can't keep her away from boys.

46:44.385 --> 46:47.309
But I just don't want her to make
the same mistake I always make,

46:47.471 --> 46:49.599
which is pick the wrong boy.

46:49.765 --> 46:52.518
She just still treats me
like I'm a child.

46:52.685 --> 46:54.938
That's lame.

46:55.104 --> 47:00.326
She was just getting wasted and trashy
and he was so nice and gentle.

47:00.484 --> 47:03.909
She didn't even care, she still talked
to him like he was a monster.

47:04.071 --> 47:06.244
That's what she does.
She picks the most damaged kid around,

47:06.407 --> 47:08.751
and then she makes them into a project.

47:08.909 --> 47:13.085
So I guess maybe I'm worried that, you
know, Ryan 's just part of that pattern.

47:15.166 --> 47:16.338
Hey.

47:18.336 --> 47:21.681
Thank you so much for coming.
I really, really wanted to apologize

47:21.839 --> 47:25.218
-for my mom last night.
- it's OK.

47:25.384 --> 47:29.105
I hope you didn't take her too
seriously. It was just classic paranoia.

47:30.389 --> 47:33.563
- This is my friend, Jillian.
- Hi.

47:34.435 --> 47:36.403
- So can you give us a ride?
- What?

47:37.229 --> 47:39.152
We're not really
supposed to do that, remember?

47:39.315 --> 47:42.945
No, my mom said she didn't want us
alone, but we're not alone.

47:44.195 --> 47:45.196
(JILLIAN SCOFFS)

47:47.281 --> 47:49.625
Yeah. Yeah, OK.

47:51.035 --> 47:54.005
SARAH: It's like I'm trying so hard
to be a good mom,

47:54.163 --> 47:58.794
for the first time,
not really doing a good job.

47:58.959 --> 48:04.090
Sarah, you're raising
a very decent girl who cares.

48:04.590 --> 48:07.013
Stop being so hard on yourself.

48:16.769 --> 48:20.569
OK, thank you for the ride home.

48:20.731 --> 48:23.701
- Bye.
- Bye, guys.

48:27.196 --> 48:29.324
(SOFT ROCK PLAYS)

48:31.492 --> 48:34.496
Again, I mention
how we're not supposed to be alone.

48:34.662 --> 48:37.006
(PHONE RING-S)

48:41.335 --> 48:43.053
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

48:45.965 --> 48:48.718
- Hey.
- Hey, I just called to tell you

48:48.884 --> 48:51.683
that I got stuck
with another late shift.

48:51.846 --> 48:54.395
So I don't think
I'm going to be back before 11.

48:54.557 --> 48:57.026
- Are you going to be OK?
- Yeah.

48:57.184 --> 48:58.857
Elissa, I need you to remember
our agreement.

48:59.019 --> 49:01.863
Yes. Don't you trust me at all?

49:06.235 --> 49:09.660
I set our home phone
to forward all her calls to my cell.

49:11.991 --> 49:13.834
You're kind of devious.

49:13.993 --> 49:15.836
I'm only trying to protect her.

49:29.383 --> 49:33.308
RYAN: Yeah, the house was actually
my great-grandfather's.

49:33.471 --> 49:38.193
Which is why it's been kind of hard
to think about selling it,

49:38.350 --> 49:41.695
you know, and the whole
fixing it up thing.

49:41.854 --> 49:44.357
But... I don't know.

49:47.026 --> 49:48.528
I want to show you something.

49:50.070 --> 49:51.242
Here, sit down.

50:01.415 --> 50:03.417
I don't remember much
when I was little.

50:04.668 --> 50:09.515
I remember my mom sitting here
and telling me everything has a secret.

50:12.384 --> 50:13.556
Everything.

50:14.553 --> 50:16.897
And at first I couldn't see it.

50:19.099 --> 50:20.646
But then one day...

50:22.228 --> 50:23.696
One day I could.

50:27.691 --> 50:29.238
See what?

50:32.112 --> 50:33.329
Look, I'll show you.

50:35.241 --> 50:36.458
LOOK.

50:48.963 --> 50:50.840
Oh, my God, it's a face.

50:54.635 --> 50:55.887
I see it.

51:00.266 --> 51:02.985
People don't notice
all the secrets around them.

51:04.103 --> 51:09.109
Even though they're right in front of
them, just hiding, waiting to be found.

51:13.862 --> 51:15.956
I like the way you see things.

51:18.325 --> 51:20.327
I like the way you see me.

51:41.849 --> 51:44.693
(SOFT ROCK PLAYS)

52:00.200 --> 52:02.999
(LAUGHING OVER INTERCOM)

52:10.377 --> 52:12.846
(MUSIC CONTINUES OVER INTERCOM)

52:32.024 --> 52:34.868
(BANGING)

52:41.408 --> 52:44.628
(BANGING)

52:57.257 --> 52:58.759
I'll be right back.

53:48.267 --> 53:50.486
- You need to leave now!
- What? Why?

53:52.730 --> 53:55.734
Ryan! Ryan!

53:55.899 --> 53:57.276
You're not supposed to be here, go!

53:57.443 --> 54:00.287
- Ryan, what did I do?
- Go! Just go! Just go home! Go!

54:14.918 --> 54:19.799
So, we'll just do it here. Come on.

54:25.596 --> 54:27.598
- (SCREAMS) Jesus Christ!
- What?

54:28.557 --> 54:30.184
- What?
- There was a girl at the window!

54:30.350 --> 54:32.068
- (MUFFLED SCREAMING)
- Sh, Sh!

54:33.937 --> 54:36.281
- Ray! Ray, come on.
- Really? Carrie Anne's outside.

54:36.440 --> 54:37.737
- OK, unbelievable.
- Ray!

54:37.900 --> 54:39.743
- (GRUNTING)
- (MUFFLED SCREAMING)

54:40.027 --> 54:42.496
- ls anyone out there?
- (SCREAMS)

54:42.654 --> 54:45.828
Carrie Anne, you're out here?
No, no, no. Come on, Alice.

54:45.991 --> 54:47.834
- Let's go find Carrie Anne.
- Ray, stop being stupid.

54:47.993 --> 54:51.998
- She's out here, right?
- (GRUNTING)

54:54.124 --> 54:56.092
- (SCREAMING) (CRACKING)

54:56.251 --> 55:00.631
- Sh! Sh!
- Ray, I want to go home!

55:01.298 --> 55:03.141
ALICE: Get back in the car, please!

55:03.884 --> 55:06.763
Carrie Anne? Carrie Anne?

55:08.388 --> 55:12.643
No... Carrie Anne, please.
Come here.

55:12.810 --> 55:14.653
(SOBBING) Wake up, wake up.

55:15.187 --> 55:17.531
Carrie Anne, please wake up.
Wake up. Wake up.

55:18.857 --> 55:23.078
Oh, God. What have I done?
What have I done?

55:57.604 --> 55:59.356
I don't know what happened.

55:59.523 --> 56:02.868
We were having so much fun,
and then he just totally freaked out.

56:03.026 --> 56:03.993
JILLIAN: What do you mean freaked out?

56:04.152 --> 56:05.119
(KNOCKING>

56:05.279 --> 56:06.622
- I have to go.
- Wait, Elissa...

56:06.780 --> 56:07.906
SARAH: Can I come in?

56:15.581 --> 56:20.382
I, uh... I wanted to apologize

56:20.544 --> 56:24.014
for the way I handled things with Ryan.

56:24.172 --> 56:26.095
It's fine, don't worry about it.

56:28.051 --> 56:33.683
You know I'm just trying to take care
of you. You know that, right?

56:33.849 --> 56:35.601
Yes.

56:37.936 --> 56:42.157
I wish sometimes
you could tell me things.

56:43.817 --> 56:45.444
That you'd let me help you.

56:47.112 --> 56:49.331
OK. I will.

56:53.869 --> 56:56.918
Um, I got you something for your show.

56:57.080 --> 56:58.297
Thank you.

56:58.457 --> 56:59.709
It's some makeup.

57:07.090 --> 57:09.764
I'm trying to do this mom thing,
you know?

57:11.553 --> 57:13.476
I know.

